channel.title: Level Numbers Help. - Very easy request! - Please look only take 3secs!
channel.description:
Hello All I am making a custom firemaking an fletching system and I don't know which number the skills are. When is say that i mean the [code] [0] [/code] thingy. What is the numbers for firemaking and fletching?
[br][br][size=1]Posted on: November 02, 2008, 03:58:13 pm[/size][hr]Oh my god can anyone help

item.title: Level Numbers Help. - Very easy request! - Please look only take 3secs!
item.dc:creator: @tonypker13 tonypker13
item.description:
@tonypker13 wrote:

Here you go.
playerLevel[0] = Attack
playerLevel[1] = Defence
playerLevel[2] = Strength
playerLevel[3] = Hitpoints
playerLevel[4] = Range
playerLevel[5] = Prayer
playerLevel[6] = Magic
playerLevel[7] = Cooking
playerLevel[8] = WoodCutting
playerLevel[9] = Fletching
playerLevel[10] = Fishing
playerLevel[11] = Firemaking
playerLevel[12] = Crafting
playerLevel[13] = Smithing
playerLevel[14] = Mining
playerLevel[15] = Herblore
playerLevel[16] = Agility
playerLevel[17] = Thieving
playerLevel[18] = Slayer
playerLevel[19] = Farming
playerLevel[20] = Runecrafting
I get these mixed up.
playerLevel[21] = Hunter. I THINK
playerLevel[22] = Summoning. I THINK.
